--- event bus
-> clean code add warning here

  The LocallyDispatchedSet uses a bounded ring buffer — it has a fixed capacity (default 8192 entries). The GC strategy is simple eviction on overflow:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        
  How it works:
  - HashSet<u64> for O(1) lookup + VecDeque<u64> for insertion order tracking                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           
  - Each entry is 8 bytes (u64 event_id), so 8192 entries = ~128KB total (set + deque)
  - When insert() is called and len >= capacity: pop the oldest entry from the front of the VecDeque, remove it from the HashSet, then insert the new one
  - Memory usage is constant — it never grows beyond capacity